# A New Window to the Stars: Why Jaegun Yoo Wants You to “Look Up”:

Kai Phung
University of Arizona

Sometimes the path to the stars begins on the living room floor.
For Jaegun Yoo, the journey to becoming a space scientist started not with a telescope, but with a screwdriver and a pile of broken toys.
As a child, he didn't just play with his things; he took them apart to see how they worked—
a curiosity that eventually led him into a career in mechanical engineering.
